<h2>decktech.net</h2><b>location of article:</b> <hr>World's 2007 Schedule of Events! posted by scott on Thu Aug 30 2007 <br><a href="http://www.swccgpc.com/forums/viewforum.php?f=238"><img src="http://www.swccgpc.com/Resources/worlds2007_100x80.bmp" align ="left"></a><br />
SWCCG Players, it's time to finalize those decks and start prepping for a run at the 2007 World Championship! <br />
<br />
Pre-registration is up on the store ready for people to get to the event now. Please pre-register now at the <a href="http://www.shop.swccgpc.com">PC Store</a>. <br />
<b>Each player that pre-registers for any event will get 2 full color virtual card printouts in Chicago.</b> <br />
<br />
The event schedule is listed below and available <a href="http://www.swccgpc.com/Resources/final2007worldsschedule.pdf">here</a>. <br />
<br />
<b>Thursday, October 4th</b> <br />
PasTimes Booster Draft Open 10:15 am - 2:30 pm <br />
Registration from 10:00 am - 10:15 am <br />
-Booster Draft Format - Reflections I <br />
-45 card decks <br />
-Four games <br />
-Top Light and Dark players get an automatic bid into Day 2 <br />
<br />
PasTimes Open 3:00 pm - 10:00 pm<br />
Registration from 2:45 pm - 3:00 pm <br />
-Endor / Death Star II Closed Environment Contructed Deck Format <br />
Tournament. Virtual Cards for legal cards allowed <br />
-Six games <br />
-Top two players get an automatic bid into Day 2 <br />
<br />
<b>Friday, October 5th</b> <br />
Worlds Day 1 10:30 am - 4:30 pm <br />
Registration from 10:00 am - 10:30 am <br />
-Open to all players not holding an automatic bid to Day 2 <br />
-Open Constructed Format <br />
-Six Games <br />
-Top 50% advance to Day 2 (minimum 4 players) <br />
<br />
Team Tournament 4:00 pm - 10:00 pm <br />
Registration from 3:45pm - 4:00 pm <br />
-Open Constructed Format <br />
-Team Format (Two players per team) <br />
-Team members will not play each other <br />
-Six Games <br />
-Top Team receives $150, Custom Mugs and automatic bids into Day 2 <br />
of 2007 (or 2008 if already qualified) World Championships <br />
-2nd Place Team receives $100 <br />
<br />
<b>Saturday, October 6th</b> <br />
2008 Invitational Qualifier 10:15 am - 6:15 pm <br />
Registration from 10:00 am to 10:15 am <br />
-Open to all players not holding an automatic bid to Day 2 <br />
-Open Constructed Deck Format <br />
-Six Games with final confrontation <br />
-1st place receives automatic bid to 2008 World Championships <br />
<br />
Worlds Day 2 11:00 am - 7:00 pm <br />
Registration from 10:30 am - 11:00 am <br />
-Entry Fee waived for players advancing from Day 1 <br />
-Open to all players qualified for Day 2 <br />
-Open Constructed Deck Format <br />
-Eight Games <br />
-Top Eight advance to Day 3 <br />
<br />
<b>Sunday, October 7th</b> <br />
Consolation Tournament 11:00 am - 7:00 pm<br />
Registration from 10:30 - 11:00 am <br />
-Open Constructed Deck Format <br />
-Six Games <br />
-1st Place receive's $150, Glass, and an automatic bid to 2008 World <br />
Championships <br />
-2nd Place receive's $100 and an automatic bid to 2008 World <br />
Championships <br />
<br />
Worlds Day 3 10:15 am - 3:15 pm</b> <br />
Registration from 10:00 am - 10:15 am <br />
-Match Play Format Constructed Deck Format <br />
-Higher seed chooses first side <br />
-Games timed to 1:15 minutes each <br />
-Top 2 players advance to Final Confrontation <br />
<br />
Worlds Final Confrontation 3:30 pm - 6:30<br />
Full Match <br />
-Games timed to 1:30 minutes each <br />
<br />
2007 Top eight prize payout <br />
-1st $1,500, World Champion Trophy and an automatic bid to 2008 <br />
World Championships <br />
-2nd $700, Runner-up Trophy <br />
-3rd $300 <br />
-4th $300 <br />
-5th $150 <br />
-6th $150 <br />
-7th $150 <br />
-8th $150 <br />
<br />
We look forward to seeing you in Chicago! Please post questions or comments here. <br />
